HEADWORD: Re-collect
<hw>Re`-col*lect"</hw> <pr>(r⟦emac⟧`k⟦ocr⟧l*l⟦ecr⟧kt")</pr>, <pos>v.
t.</pos> <ety>[Pref. <ets>re-</ets> + <ets>collect</ets>.]</ety> <def>To
collect again; to gather what has been scattered; <as>as, to
<ex>re-collect</ex> routed troops</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>God will one day raise the dead, <qex>re-collecting</qex> our
scattered dust.</q> <rj><qau>Barrow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Recollect</ent>⟦br⟧
